subject: [WIP] Add I2C statistics
commitMessage:
[WIP] Add I2C statistics

This is a WIP.

The I2C statistics are intended to be used with Redfish resources:

ManagerDiagnosticData.I2CBuses.I2CBusName
ManagerDiagnosticData.I2CBuses.TotalTransactionCount
ManagerDiagnosticData.I2CBuses.BusErrorCount
ManagerDiagnosticData.I2CBuses.NACKCount

Notes:

1) This change will not build unless the I2CStats interfaces have been
added to phosphor-dbus-interfaces and the change
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/45683
is merged. This change currently serves the purpose for helping
discussing how the I2C statistics should be maintained as they add new
code paths to phosphor-health-monitor.

2) Currently, the I2C statistics are only available on NPCM7XX I2C
controllers, because only this device exports those statistics. This
device exports the statistics to debugfs. We have reached out to the
LKML about adding mechanisms to allow I2C controller drivers to export
counters to sysfs, allowing a unified interface across different I2C
controllers, but we haven't received a concrete answer from them yet.

Change-Id: Ib29221d0b2b4f8bb60748ff0f4bf110a68b8419d
Signed-off-by: Sui Chen <suichen@google.com>
